Package lab5.smallStore

Provides the necessary classes for the specific smallStore.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Closes
    The Class Closes represents the event of the store closing
    CustomerArrives
    The Class CustomerArrives represents the event of a customer arriving to the store.
    CustomerPays
    The Class CustomerPays represents the event of a customer paying at the register.
    FIFO
    The class FIFO represents a queue system based an the "First In First Out" system
    Opens
    The Class Opens represents the event that the store opens
    ShopGoods
    The Class ShopGoods represents the event of a customer shopping for goods in the store When the performEvent is called the state is changed and the customer has shopped.
    SmallStoreState
    The Class SmallStoreState keeps track of the state of the simulation Every time the state changes SmallStoreView gets updated
    SmallStoreView  
    TimeKeeper
    Keeps track of the time and creates new dynamic objects from the classes UniformRandomStream and ExponentialRandomStream
